==English==

===Etymology===
Latin, from ancient Greek ''apsinthion'', from ''apsinthos''. The Greek word is of uncertain origin. May be from Persian ''aspand'', ''spand'' ("wormwood").

===Noun===
#''(Botany):'' The common [[wormwood]] (''[[Artemisia]] absinthium''), an [[intensely]] bitter plant, used as a [[tonic]] and for making the oil of wormwood.

